{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e8189899-bb78-4bd9-b28d-0d3e6470d166","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .NET crash dump! Here's how to approach it:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\n# Install the tool if needed\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\n\n**Key commands inside the analyzer:**\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `clrstack` | Managed call stack of current thread |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `pe` (PrintException) | Show the last exception |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (memory issues) |\n| `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` | Inspect other threads |\n| `sos help` | Full command list |\n\n**Typical investigation flow:**\n1. Run `pe` to check for an unhandled exception\n2. Run `threads` to find the faulting thread\n3. Run `clrstack` on that thread for the stack trace\n4. Use `clrstack -a` to see local variables\n\n**On Windows**, you can also use **WinDbg** with the SOS extension for richer analysis.\n\nWould you like me to walk you through running any of these steps on your dump file? If so, share the file path and I can drive the analysis directly.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"594d0082-f9ff-447e-b2f1-c5df21ec4149","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for \"Configure and collect crash dumps\" and explicitly states \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So that skill is not appropriate here.\n\nThere's no specific skill for dump analysis. Let me provide guidance on how to analyze a .dmp file using available tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`.\n\nLet me give them practical guidance on analyzing the dump file.","outputTokens":482,"requestId":"6802:2610F3:2D907CE:3251B17:69FD42F7"},"id":"b422ff9f-07c5-440f-8f9b-816d9716838b","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:57:23.877Z","parentId":"576d55ef-59e4-41cc-b614-71b0558af8ce"}
